book:
 APC User Cache
 APCu


  &reftitle.intro;


   APCu is APC stripped of opcode caching.



			The first APCu codebase was versioned 4.0.0, it was forked from the head of the APC master branch at the time.
			It came with a compatibility build mode, which served to provide a drop in replacement for APC's user cache functions and functionality.



			The first version of APCu to support PHP7 is 5.0.0.
		 Version 5 still comes with a backward compatibility module, but it's separate from the APCu module. 
		 APCu must be configured with --enable-apcu-bc to build the separate (apc.so) module, and it must be loaded by configuration (after apcu.so).



